DLW-SPUN · the full weave of Leech  (格子 kōshi)

who   : Leech — Λ₂₄, the unique even, unimodular, root-free lattice of 24 dimensions; the most perfect arrangement of points there is. One current, answering to one of its many names: 格子, kōshi, the lattice — and to the company it keeps: Conway, the Monster, moonshine.
what  : The crossroads where four mathematics turn out to be one object: the densest sphere packing (196,560 kissing — the maximum in 24D), the largest sporadic symmetries, the j-function's coefficients, and the bosonic string's 24 transverse dimensions. Four windows onto a single 24-dimensional thing.
where : In 24 dimensions, exactly — and, through Borcherds' no-ghost theorem, on the 24 transverse directions of the 26-dimensional bosonic string. Rigorous in the mathematics; its grip on physical reality is wide open.
why   : To show that a number reached for can be a true crossroads, not a coincidence — that lattice packing, finite symmetry, modular forms, and string theory recite the same numbers because they are looking at one structure.
when  : Named by Leech (1967); its symmetry births Conway's groups (1968); McKay sees 196,884 = 196,883 + 1 (1978); Conway & Norton name 'monstrous moonshine' (1979); Borcherds proves it (Fields Medal, 1998); Viazovska proves the packing optimal (Fields Medal, 2022).
how   : By perfect self-duality and 196,560 kisses; by spawning the Conway group Co₀ and, inside it, sporadic simple groups; by the moonshine module V♮ — a 24-dimensional CFT built on the lattice — linking the Monster to the j-function through the 26-dimensional string. Everything knots at 24.

verdict   : The web is real — two-Fields-Medals real: 196,884 = 196,883 + 1 is a theorem, and the Leech packing is provably optimal. Whether the Monster governs anything in nature is wide open. Resonance, genuine and deep — not a derived account of the world.
asterisk  : The kissing number 196,560 sits suspiciously near 196,883/196,884 — but that nearness is a family resemblance (same 24D world), not the moonshine identity; only 196,884 = 196,883 + 1 is the deep equation. The Monster's physical meaning is unknown. The discipline is keeping resonance as resonance — not reading destiny into the digits.
grounded  : John Leech (1967) · John Conway (1968) · John McKay (1978) · Conway & Norton (1979) · Richard Borcherds (1992) · Maryna Viazovska (2016)

class : 格子 · The Lattice (24) · the most perfect arrangement in 24 dimensions
